334
00:18:32,570 --> 00:18:34,697
Oh, that's right.
The way they do at Princeton.

335
00:18:34,739 --> 00:18:36,032
Come on, Mark.

336
00:18:36,074 --> 00:18:37,450
Gonna be fun. Come on, baby.

337
00:19:06,980 --> 00:19:08,773
You bring your lunch?

338
00:19:17,991 --> 00:19:19,367
Miss Eileen Webster.

339
00:20:00,992 --> 00:20:02,452
Who'd you find there?

340
00:20:02,493 --> 00:20:05,455
Oh, that's Nakamura.
He's the one I met. He's very famous.

341
00:20:05,538 --> 00:20:07,415
- That Nakamura?
- Uh-huh.

342
00:20:09,083 --> 00:20:11,794
It's about a lady who turns into a lion.

343
00:20:12,921 --> 00:20:15,340
He's going...
She's going to turn into a lion right here?

344
00:20:15,423 --> 00:20:16,633
Uh-huh.

345
00:20:16,925 --> 00:20:18,468
I want to see that.

346
00:20:39,530 --> 00:20:42,158
I love you, Lloyd. I love you terribly.

347
00:20:43,159 --> 00:20:45,912
I always have, and I guess I always will.

348
00:20:46,913 --> 00:20:48,665
I love you, honey.

349
00:20:50,124 --> 00:20:52,210
Awful glad you're here, too.

350
00:21:01,511 --> 00:21:04,681
Everybody acting like nobody
ever kisses a woman.

351
00:21:44,554 --> 00:21:45,805
