if she didn't stick her face
in that flour barrel.

353
00:21:48,558 --> 00:21:49,642
She?

354
00:21:50,893 --> 00:21:52,770
Well, whatever it was.

355
00:21:54,188 --> 00:21:55,565
You got me.

356
00:22:03,573 --> 00:22:05,325
He's a male actress.

357
00:22:05,408 --> 00:22:08,202
It says here they've been
trained since childhood

358
00:22:08,244 --> 00:22:09,579
to have the grace of a woman,

359
00:22:09,620 --> 00:22:10,997
and yet the power of a man.

360
00:22:11,080 --> 00:22:12,415
Oh, my word.

361
00:22:15,084 --> 00:22:17,086
My Lord, that's my father!

362
00:22:45,573 --> 00:22:48,076
Is he man enough now for you, Lloyd?

363
00:22:49,660 --> 00:22:51,621
Is that the same fellow?

364
00:22:51,704 --> 00:22:52,914
Uh-huh.

365
00:23:11,933 --> 00:23:13,476
All right, boy.

366
00:23:23,694 --> 00:23:27,156
I am sure it must be very difficult

367
00:23:27,198 --> 00:23:30,827
to enjoy theater so different from your own.

368
00:23:31,411 --> 00:23:33,454
Well, we found it fascinating.

369
00:23:33,496 --> 00:23:34,831
I am glad.

370
00:23:35,790 --> 00:23:37,500
Kabuki is very old, isn't it?

371
00:23:37,834 --> 00:23:40,628
Mmm. Some 300 years.

372
00:23:41,671 --> 00:23:45,133
I find myself becoming intrigued
by everything in Japan.

373
00:23:45,591 --> 00:23:48,594
I should be happy to help you
know my country better

374
00:23:48,678 --> 00:23:50,471
if at any time I can.

375
00:23:52,515 --> 00:23:57,019
You did not enjoy the evening
so much, I fear, Major Gruver.

376
00:23:57,353 --> 00:24:00,022
Oh, yeah, I thought it was a fine play.

377
00:24:01,566 --> 00:24:05,570
I thought maybe you could use a Marilyn
Monroe here and there, you know, to...

378
00:24:09,532 --> 00:24:12,952
Unfortunately, Miss Monroes were barred

379
00:24:13,035 --> 00:24:15,371
from Kabuki in the 17th century.

380
00:24:17,248 --> 00:24:18,541
Well, I didn't mean to sound corny.

381
00:24:18,624 --> 00:24:21,127
I just didn't know what to say about it.

382
00:24:21,335 --> 00:24:23,463
Oh, please, do not apologize.

383
00:24:23,629 --> 00:24:28,426
I am great admirer of Miss Monroe myself.

384
00:24:29,343 --> 00:24:32,054
That's two of us. That's you and me, boy.

385
00:24:36,309 --> 00:24:38,060
- Oh, no, don't do it to me.
- Oh, no, thank you.

386
00:24:38,102 --> 00:24:40,688
I did real good. Thank you very much.

387
00:24:41,481 --> 00:24:43,608
- Fine art.
-Let's go and see the garden.

388
00:24:43,691 --> 00:24:45,693
Okay, you go on. I'll take this.

389
00:24:47,361 --> 00:24:50,781
That's fine. Fine cooking. Very good.

390
00:24:58,915 --> 00:25:00,666
Here you are, honey.

391
00:25:01,375 --> 00:25:03,794
-No, thank you.
- Don't care for any?

392
00:25:05,087 --> 00:25:06,255
Sit down, darling.

393
00:25:06,297 --> 00:25:08,424
Mmm, you look awful pretty.

394
00:25:13,012 --> 00:25:15,932
I've been doing a lot of thinking
with you away, Lloyd.

395
00:25:16,015 --> 00:25:17,433
Answer me one thing.

396
00:25:17,517 --> 00:25:19,185
What's that, honey?

397
00:25:19,268 --> 00:25:21,270
Why aren't we married now?

398
00:25:22,605 --> 00:25:24,774
Isn't that a silly question?

399
00:25:24,857 --> 00:25:26,400
No, not really.

400
00:25:26,609 --> 00:25:29,070
You do a lot of wondering in Tulsa.

401
00:25:29,487 --> 00:25:31,030
Mmm, I suppose

402
00:25:31,113 --> 00:25:33,741
the Korean War might have a little
something to do with it, don't you think?

403
00:25:33,783 --> 00:25:36,953
Wasn't Korea maybe convenient, Lloyd?

404
00:25:37,620 --> 00:25:38,913
Convenient?

405
00:25:38,955 --> 00:25:40,873
What I really mean is,

406
00:25:41,749 --> 00:25:45,086
do I mean everything to you,
as you do to me?

407
00:25:45,127 --> 00:25:46,671
Of course you do, hon.
What are you talking about?

408
00:25:46,754 --> 00:25:48,631
You see, I went to visit your mother

409
00:25:48,673 --> 00:25:50,925
before I came here, there in Richmond.

410
00:25:50,967 --> 00:25:52,051
My mother?

411
00:25:52,134 --> 00:25:55,388
I was appalled at the loneliness
in which she lives

412
00:25:55,471 --> 00:25:57,807
and the way your father is content to go off

413
00:25:57,848 --> 00:25:59,850
and leave her walled up
within a circle of friends

414
00:25:59,934 --> 00:26:02,144
while he plunges off to the war...

415
00:26:02,228 --> 00:26:04,188
Oh, honey, now, you just hold on a second.

416
00:26:04,272 --> 00:26:05,523
You got to remember something.

417
00:26:05,606 --> 00:26:07,650
My father's a general, honey.

418
00:26:07,733 --> 00:26:09,902
And besides that,
my mother wants to live that way.

419
00:26:09,986 --> 00:26:11,445
Oh, don't be ridiculous.

420
00:26:11,487 --> 00:26:12,822
What do you mean? Now, don't tell me...

421
00:26:12,905 --> 00:26:14,907
No woman wants to live any way except

422
00:26:14,991 --> 00:26:17,493
body and soul with the man she loves.

423
00:26:18,578 --> 00:26:19,870
Lloyd, you'll never tuck me away

424
00:26:19,954 --> 00:26:21,581
in the corner of some little town.

425
00:26:21,664 --> 00:26:23,165
Go ahead and become the greatest general

426
00:26:23,207 --> 00:26:25,501
in Air Force history, but love me, too.

427
00:26:25,543 --> 00:26:28,045
But I do love you, baby, I do.

428
00:26:30,673 --> 00:26:33,593
Well, I guess all I'm trying to say is that,

429
00:26:34,302 --> 00:26:36,596
and I really mean this, Lloyd,

430
00:26:37,346 --> 00:26:40,933
if what you want is a family
like our fathers have,

431
00:26:42,059 --> 00:26:44,437
and promotion in the Air Force,

432
00:26:44,520 --> 00:26:47,523
and position in society
like our mothers have,

433
00:26:48,274 --> 00:26:50,860
and you marry me
because I'm pretty and smart

434
00:26:50,943 --> 00:26:53,529
and have guts and will know the ropes,

435
00:26:57,199 --> 00:27:00,244
then I don't think
you ought to marry me, Lloyd.

436
00:27:01,537 --> 00:27:04,874
I'm sorry.
I guess I've been thinking too much.

437
00:27:06,876 --> 00:27:10,004
Yeah, I think you have
been thinking too much.

438
00:27:27,772 --> 00:27:31,025
Now. Now, quit it.

439
00:27:32,318 --> 00:27:33,402
Okay-

440
00:27:34,362 --> 00:27:36,489
Oh, I don't know, maybe things
will turn out after all.

441
00:27:36,572 --> 00:27:38,240
What do you mean
maybe it's going to turn out?

442
00:27:38,324 --> 00:27:39,659
Sure it's gonna turn out.

443
00:27:39,742 --> 00:27:41,619
It's just all that nonsense you talk about

444
00:27:41,702 --> 00:27:43,746
every time we get together.

445
00:27:44,413 --> 00:27:47,917
Nonsense? I...
I hadn't realized it was nonsense.

446
00:27:48,250 --> 00:27:49,502
Of course it is, honey.

447
00:27:49,585 --> 00:27:51,212
Listen, it's all very simple.

448
00:27:51,253 --> 00:27:52,672
Now, lookit.

449
00:27:53,214 --> 00:27:56,425
I want a wife and a family.

450
00:27:56,509 --> 00:27:58,427
I want a home in America.

451
00:27:58,469 --> 00:28:00,471
And every time I think of
having a home like that,

452
00:28:00,554 --> 00:28:03,474
I always think about it with a girl like you.

453
00:28:03,808 --> 00:28:06,394
I mean, a girl with a good
Army background like my own.

454
00:28:06,435 --> 00:28:10,314
What do you mean a girl like me?
I'm not a type. I'm me.

455
00:28:10,981 --> 00:28:13,609
Oh, Lloyd, it's me you've got to love.

456
00:28:15,027 --> 00:28:16,696
Oh, Lloyd, haven't you ever felt

457
00:28:16,779 --> 00:28:18,364
like grabbing me

458
00:28:18,447 --> 00:28:20,825
and hauling me off to a shack somewhere?

459
00:28:20,908 --> 00:28:22,034
What's the matter with you?

460
00:28:22,118 --> 00:28:23,911
You know better than that.
Of course I have.

461
00:28:23,953 --> 00:28:25,454
Then what's holding you back?

462
00:28:25,496 --> 00:28:27,456
Oh, Eileen,
are you ever going to grow up, honey?

463
00:28:27,540 --> 00:28:28,999
Don't you know there's a right time

464
00:28:29,083 --> 00:28:30,793
and a wrong time to do things?

465
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:32,002
Aren't you ever gonna realize

466
00:28:32,086 --> 00:28:33,796
that you have responsibilities
to other people,

467
00:28:33,838 --> 00:28:35,631
that you have a position to fulfill,

468
00:28:35,673 --> 00:28:37,633
that you're not alone in this world?

469
00:28:37,675 --> 00:28:39,677
Oh, you defend yourself like a fort!

470
00:28:39,760 --> 00:28:41,470
Listen, no matter how I defend myself,

471
00:28:41,512 --> 00:28:42,805
hon, you've got to understand one thing,

472
00:28:42,888 --> 00:28:44,765
that I am not in a position

473
00:28:44,807 --> 00:28:47,977
to be hauling my fiancee away
to a shack somewhere

474
00:28:48,018 --> 00:28:49,603
like an alley cat or something like that.

475
00:28:49,645 --> 00:28:51,814
I wasn't brought up that way.

476
00:28:51,981 --> 00:28:54,066
