502
00:30:16,982 --> 00:30:18,400
You'll look after your wife on your own.

503
00:30:18,442 --> 00:30:20,402
The Air Force is not responsible.

504
00:30:21,070 --> 00:30:22,905
Yeah, I know.

505
00:30:22,988 --> 00:30:24,782
Romantic, ain't it, Major?

506
00:30:26,700 --> 00:30:28,702
Will you finish this ugly deed
and get it over?

507
00:30:30,120 --> 00:30:32,414
I now pronounce you man and wife.
Sign over there.

508
00:30:32,748 --> 00:30:34,333
Just a minute.

509
00:30:53,435 --> 00:30:55,145
That's it, Mrs. Kelly.

510
00:30:55,813 --> 00:30:57,606
Just you and me now.

511
00:31:09,076 --> 00:31:10,160
Where do we sign?

512
00:31:11,537 --> 00:31:13,789
May as well witness this now, Major.

513
00:31:14,164 --> 00:31:15,541
Yeah, all right.

514
00:31:18,294 --> 00:31:20,629
Incidentally, it was a great honor
meeting you, Major Gruver.

515
00:31:20,713 --> 00:31:21,797
Well, thank you.

516
00:31:22,673 --> 00:31:24,341
Say, tell me, Consul,

517
00:31:25,467 --> 00:31:28,095
are all these ceremonies
conducted like that?

518
00:31:28,345 --> 00:31:31,807
Well, we do our best
to prevent as many as possible.

519
00:31:32,558 --> 00:31:34,143
We make the paperwork so difficult,

520
00:31:34,226 --> 00:31:35,811
a good many of them lose steam.

521
00:31:35,853 --> 00:31:37,187
Uh-huh.

522
00:31:37,646 --> 00:31:39,899
Well, about how many, uh...

523
00:31:40,316 --> 00:31:43,485
About how many Gis have gone
through this ceremony?

524
00:31:44,737 --> 00:31:48,616
Oh, about 10,000.

525
00:31:49,450 --> 00:31:53,120
Ten thousand? Well, then,
you let a few slip by you, didn't you?

526
00:31:53,162 --> 00:31:54,288
A few, yes.

527
00:31:54,330 --> 00:31:55,331
Mmm-hmm.

528
00:31:56,832 --> 00:31:58,250
How's your girl, Major?

529
00:31:59,251 --> 00:32:00,669
Oh, Eileen?

530
00:32:01,003 --> 00:32:02,296
I haven't seen her in a couple days.

531
00:32:02,338 --> 00:32:05,674
I've been... You know, I've been moving in,
getting my things arranged.

532
00:32:06,884 --> 00:32:10,095
And she's been hightailing it
with the brass, socializing.

533
00:32:11,513 --> 00:32:12,765
Major,

534
00:32:12,848 --> 00:32:14,433
ain't you going to kiss the bride?

535
00:32:16,226 --> 00:32:17,770
Well, sure I'm going to kiss the bride!

536
00:32:19,480 --> 00:32:20,606
Yeah.

537
00:32:21,357 --> 00:32:22,399
Sure.

538
00:32:23,150 --> 00:32:26,820
Now, listen, I want you
to take good care of this boy, hear?

539
00:32:30,616 --> 00:32:33,202
Now, here's your ticket, honey.
Don't forget it.

540
00:32:35,746 --> 00:32:36,872
Okay, boy.

541
00:32:39,375 --> 00:32:40,709
Thanks, Major.

542
00:32:40,751 --> 00:32:42,419
Took a lot of guts for you
to come here today.

543
00:32:42,628 --> 00:32:44,046
Oh, quit.

544
00:32:44,296 --> 00:32:46,882
If you want anybody taken care of,
or need a job done

545
00:32:46,966 --> 00:32:48,384
that you West Point guys ain't allowed

546
00:32:48,467 --> 00:32:49,802
to do yourselves, I'm your man.

547
00:32:50,052 --> 00:32:52,471
Hold it. Now, I'm going to call on you, boy.

548
00:32:52,554 --> 00:32:53,681
Come on. Let's get a belt.

549
00:32:53,722 --> 00:32:54,765
All right.

550
00:32:55,474 --> 00:32:56,642
-Nice to see you.
- How are you, Lloyd, dear?

551
00:32:56,725 --> 00:32:58,477
Fine. Just fine.

552
00:32:58,560 --> 00:32:59,812
That's a pretty dress you got on.

553
00:32:59,895 --> 00:33:01,105
Thanks.

554
00:33:01,438 --> 00:33:03,065
Lloyd, sit down, son.

555
00:33:03,565 --> 00:33:04,692
All right.

556
00:33:08,487 --> 00:33:10,114
Thank you for coming over
so promptly, Lloyd.

557
00:33:10,197 --> 00:33:13,242
Well, that's all right.
I was just darning my socks.

558
00:33:13,325 --> 00:33:15,327
Lloyd, um...

559
00:33:16,662 --> 00:33:18,914
I don't know exactly how to put this.

560
00:33:18,956 --> 00:33:21,583
It's a little embarrassing, for me, that is.

561
00:33:22,710 --> 00:33:25,963
I understand you were a witness
at a marriage yesterday

562
00:33:26,088 --> 00:33:28,632
between one of your men
and a Japanese girl.

563
00:33:30,259 --> 00:33:33,637
Yeah, one man from my outfit in Korea.

564
00:33:34,430 --> 00:33:38,058
Well, you realize, of course,
there's an Army policy

565
00:33:38,100 --> 00:33:39,852
to discourage all such marriages.

566
00:33:40,477 --> 00:33:42,438
Yeah, well, I think they couldn't
have been discouraged.

567
00:33:42,521 --> 00:33:44,606
They're very much in love, and...

568
00:33:46,442 --> 00:33:48,027
I dare say.

569
00:33:48,485 --> 00:33:50,821
However, the fact that you personally

570
00:33:50,904 --> 00:33:52,072
seemed to sanction the marriage...

571
00:33:52,156 --> 00:33:55,784
Oh, no, no.
I didn't mean to give that impression at all.

572
00:33:55,868 --> 00:33:57,411
I didn't sanction it, and as a matter of fact,

573
00:33:57,453 --> 00:33:59,204
I tried to talk him out of it before.

574
00:33:59,496 --> 00:34:01,957
But, Lloyd, darling,
you did act as his witness.

575
00:34:03,542 --> 00:34:04,543
Well...

576
00:34:05,085 --> 00:34:07,129
You know, as long as
it's going to be inevitable,

577
00:34:07,212 --> 00:34:09,673
I thought I might as well try
to make it as pleasant as possible.

578
00:34:10,049 --> 00:34:12,134
Don't you see the position that puts me in?

579
00:34:12,551 --> 00:34:15,304
And since I'm the Area Commander here, I...

580
00:34:15,345 --> 00:34:18,140
No, you didn't do anything
to encourage this marriage, sir.

581
00:34:18,182 --> 00:34:20,350
I believe I did all this on my own.

582
00:34:20,434 --> 00:34:24,480
What do you mean on your own,
Lloyd, dear?

583
00:34:24,521 --> 00:34:26,815
Everything you do reflects on the General.

584
00:34:26,899 --> 00:34:28,901
After all, he is Eileen’s father.

585
00:34:29,693 --> 00:34:32,613
I'm afraid this places me in a position
of incompetence, Mrs. Webster,

586
00:34:32,654 --> 00:34:36,200
when it comes to, you know,
doing anything to help my own men.

587
00:34:37,284 --> 00:34:39,495
Let's stop beating around the bush.

588
00:34:39,870 --> 00:34:41,914
What's wrong between you and Eileen?

589
00:34:41,997 --> 00:34:44,708
You haven't been to see her
for several days.

590
00:34:48,962 --> 00:34:49,963
Well,

591
00:34:51,048 --> 00:34:54,426
you talked about
being embarrassed, sir, before.

592
00:34:54,760 --> 00:34:56,303
I'm embarrassed, too.

593
00:34:57,387 --> 00:35:00,516
- What about?
- Well, about my whole situation here.

594
00:35:01,100 --> 00:35:04,186
I'm a pilot, sir. I was doing a job in Korea.

595
00:35:04,228 --> 00:35:07,648
Unfinished job. Now, suddenly,
I'm pulled off that job and sent over here

596
00:35:07,689 --> 00:35:11,652
and plunked down at a desk
at this Interservice whatever it is,

597
00:35:11,693 --> 00:35:13,195
and, you know, where, as far as I can see,

598
00:35:13,278 --> 00:35:15,280
there's absolutely nothing to do.

599
00:35:15,364 --> 00:35:17,407
You know, all so as I can be with Eileen.

600
00:35:18,117 --> 00:35:19,827
There's nothing dishonest about it.

601
00:35:19,868 --> 00:35:21,829
That is, if you plan to get married.

602
00:35:22,287 --> 00:35:25,374
I think I know how Lloyd feels.

603
00:35:25,415 --> 00:35:27,292
Do you plan to get married or not?

604
00:35:27,376 --> 00:35:30,546
-Really, dear.
- Well, I'm her mother. I want to know.

605
00:35:33,132 --> 00:35:34,925
Well, Mrs. Webster,

606
00:35:35,008 --> 00:35:37,845
as of the moment,
Eileen isn't too sure about it.

607
00:35:38,178 --> 00:35:39,346
And I...

608
00:35:39,680 --> 00:35:42,349
Oh, we know, Lloyd, dear. Now, look.

609
00:35:42,891 --> 00:35:45,978
There's evidently been some
slight strain between you two,

610
00:35:46,061 --> 00:35:48,230
but don't let it become too important.

611
00:35:48,313 --> 00:35:51,108
Now, this is Sunday night.
Why don't you call her up later

612
00:35:51,191 --> 00:35:53,569
and ask her out to dinner or something?

613
00:35:53,777 --> 00:35:54,903
Well...

614
00:35:54,987 --> 00:35:57,739
Mother, I found the dearest little shop at...

615
00:35:58,866 --> 00:35:59,950
Hi, Lloyd.

616
00:36:00,367 --> 00:36:01,785
Hello, Eileen.

617
00:36:01,869 --> 00:36:04,079
Lloyd just came in to see you.

618
00:36:04,538 --> 00:36:06,039
-Oh?
- Oh, yeah.

619
00:36:07,708 --> 00:36:09,585
Listen...

620
00:36:10,752 --> 00:36:13,922
Listen, I thought
Sunday night, and I thought maybe

621
00:36:14,006 --> 00:36:16,842
you and I can go out
and catch a movie or something.

622
00:36:17,926 --> 00:36:19,261
Feel like it?

623
00:36:20,262 --> 00:36:23,765
I'm sorry, Lloyd.
I'm having dinner with some friends tonight.

624
00:36:24,057 --> 00:36:25,058
Well,

625
00:36:25,934 --> 00:36:27,477
what about tomorrow?

626
00:36:28,395 --> 00:36:30,189
That's booked, too, I'm afraid.

627
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:36,111
Well, looks as though
I'm holding some pretty tough cards.

628
00:36:39,615 --> 00:36:42,117
What about next week?

629
00:36:43,785 --> 00:36:45,829
Of course, Lloyd. Call me?

630
00:36:48,832 --> 00:36:49,958
Okay-

631
00:36:53,378 --> 00:36:55,172
Mrs. Webster, General.

632
00:36:56,298 --> 00:36:57,299
Goodbye, Lloyd.

633
00:36:57,341 --> 00:36:59,134
- Bye, Eileen.
- Bye, Lloyd.

634
00:37:06,183 --> 00:37:09,353
Oh, Eileen. Why did you tell him
you were busy tonight?

635
00:37:12,064 --> 00:37:15,859
Because I don't want to see Lloyd Gruver
when you ask him to see me.

636
00:37:16,485 --> 00:37:17,653
Besides,

637
00:37:18,070 --> 00:37:19,821
I do have a date with that young Lieutenant

638
00:37:19,863 --> 00:37:21,823
and his wife from Fort Bragg.

639
00:37:21,865 --> 00:37:23,575
Whole bunch of us.

640
00:37:30,540 --> 00:37:32,793
I hope you don't lose my man for me.

641
00:37:55,148 --> 00:37:56,525
Boy, give me a martini, will you?

642
00:37:58,819 --> 00:38:00,487
Nope, make it lemonade.

643
00:38:02,322 --> 00:38:04,658
No, dog. Give me a scotch and soda.

644
00:38:05,534 --> 00:38:06,702
- Scotch and soda.
- -Yeah.

645
00:38:07,202 --> 00:38:08,912
Scotch and soda, sir.

646
00:38:09,204 --> 00:38:11,790
There's such a thing as insolence
through manner, you know.

647
00:38:19,047 --> 00:38:21,967
Well, I hate to admit it,
but I guess that's what I said.

648
00:38:24,219 --> 00:38:26,179
Well, I thought it sounded kind of strange

649
00:38:26,221 --> 00:38:28,598
coming from a guy
who shot down nine MiGs.

650
00:38:29,975 --> 00:38:31,310
Well, that's kind of a reflex action.

651
00:38:31,393 --> 00:38:33,061
I'm a West Point man, you know.

652
00:38:33,395 --> 00:38:36,231
I guess, it sneaks out sometimes.

653
00:38:39,401 --> 00:38:41,320
Now, listen, Captain, what does a fellow do

654
00:38:41,403 --> 00:38:43,405
around here after the sun goes down?

655
00:38:44,740 --> 00:38:45,782
Why?

656
00:38:46,199 --> 00:38:47,242
You on the loose?

657
00:38:47,576 --> 00:38:49,494
Uh... Halfway.

658
00:38:50,662 --> 00:38:52,080
Bring him another.

659
00:38:53,623 --> 00:38:55,876
What part of the South are you from?

660
00:38:56,710 --> 00:38:59,296
Almost any old place
that's got an Army post on it.

661
00:39:01,089 --> 00:39:03,925
I was all set to take the exams at West Point

662
00:39:04,217 --> 00:39:06,261
and there was a teacher there

663
00:39:06,970 --> 00:39:09,473
who made me take a part in a school play.

664
00:39:09,765 --> 00:39:13,143
They were doing one of those
Hungarian things by Molnar.

665
00:39:15,103 --> 00:39:17,105
You never did hear a Hungarian play

666
00:39:17,147 --> 00:39:19,107
played in a Southern accent, did you?

667
00:39:19,441 --> 00:39:21,068
No, I'm afraid I missed that.

668
00:39:21,109 --> 00:39:23,862
That's a shame,
because I was awful good in it.

669
00:39:24,571 --> 00:39:28,617
Anyhow, I suddenly didn't want
to go to West Point

670
00:39:29,493 --> 00:39:31,620
and didn't want
to have anything to do with it.

671
00:39:31,703 --> 00:39:33,997
And my mother come up to the school,

672
00:39:35,499 --> 00:39:38,293
and she said,
"We always expected you to go to the Point

673
00:39:38,377 --> 00:39:41,296
"like your father and his father before him."

674
00:39:41,630 --> 00:39:43,882
And I told her,

675
00:39:43,965 --> 00:39:48,512
I said I had an idea about
a whole different way of life.

676
00:39:49,346 --> 00:39:50,680
What did she say to that?

677
00:39:51,515 --> 00:39:53,475
She said something like,

678
00:39:54,393 --> 00:39:56,228
"If I ever once had that idea,

679
00:39:56,311 --> 00:39:58,730
"I shouldn't let anything stop me."

680
00:39:59,731 --> 00:40:04,486
And she couldn't come right out and say,
"Don't go to the Point."

681
00:40:04,528 --> 00:40:06,571
You know, but I know what she meant.

682
00:40:07,739 --> 00:40:10,242
Then, of course,
my father flew up from Texas and...

683
00:40:10,700 --> 00:40:11,827
He put you straight, huh?

684
00:40:12,786 --> 00:40:15,705
No, he just looked at me and said,

685
00:40:15,789 --> 00:40:18,917
"If you don't want to go to the Point,
don't go to the Point.

686
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:21,628
"The unhappiest men I know are those

687
00:40:23,213 --> 00:40:26,758
"who are forced into something
they got no inaptitude for."

688
00:40:27,175 --> 00:40:29,886
How did he force you to go to the Point?

689
00:40:30,470 --> 00:40:33,056
That's what I'm telling you.
He didn't force me. He just...

690
00:40:33,140 --> 00:40:36,351
We just had a little talk,
and he flew back to Texas

691
00:40:36,393 --> 00:40:38,520
and I went on to the Point.

692
00:40:40,147 --> 00:40:41,314
I see.

693
00:40:41,898 --> 00:40:44,651
Well, uh, I'll tell you
something though, Mike.

694
00:40:46,194 --> 00:40:49,656
I never once had any regrets
about going to the Point.

695
00:40:50,407 --> 00:40:52,284
Except, just lately,

696
00:40:52,659 --> 00:40:55,454
I've had some old feeling come back on me.

697
00:40:56,329 --> 00:40:57,914
I don't know if I want to go on

698
00:40:57,998 --> 00:41:00,917
in the Air Force and buck for a star

699
00:41:01,001 --> 00:41:03,128
and get married in the Webster family

700
00:41:03,211 --> 00:41:05,547
and get swallowed up by all that.

701
00:41:07,382 --> 00:41:09,885
I think maybe my old lady was right.

702
00:41:11,470 --> 00:41:13,346
Well, what does it all mean?

703
00:41:15,098 --> 00:41:17,893
Eternal struggle, sex,

704
00:41:18,935 --> 00:41:20,562
New York Yankees.

705
00:41:21,021 --> 00:41:23,440
All right. Quit, now. Come on.

706
00:41:32,741 --> 00:41:34,993
Isn't that a nice-looking bridge?

707
00:41:35,076 --> 00:41:36,828
Yeah,
that's the Bitchi-Bashi.

708
00:41:37,204 --> 00:41:38,246
Say what?

709
00:41:38,288 --> 00:41:39,998
The Bitchi-Bashi.

710
00:41:40,081 --> 00:41:42,375
Bashi is Japanese for "bridge."

711
00:41:42,417 --> 00:41:45,128
We call this particular one the Bitchi-Bashi

712
00:41:45,212 --> 00:41:48,632
because there's so much
lovely stuff that goes over it.

713
00:41:49,925 --> 00:41:51,593
Did you say stuff?

714
00:41:52,260 --> 00:41:54,095
Brother, I said stuff.

715
00:41:55,805 --> 00:41:59,351
Will you kindly tell me what
we're standing in the bushes for?

716
00:41:59,434 --> 00:42:01,603
-Can't touch it.
- Why not?

717
00:42:01,686 --> 00:42:05,774
Well, you see, these girls that go over there
are the Matsubayashi girls.

718
00:42:06,024 --> 00:42:08,151
They just cross over there
on the way to the theater

719
00:42:08,235 --> 00:42:11,279
from those cells over there,
those dormitories.

720
00:42:11,738 --> 00:42:14,115
Oh, that's right.
Somebody told me about that.

721
00:42:16,076 --> 00:42:19,454
Hey, boy, is that anything
going over there now?

722
00:42:22,457 --> 00:42:24,543
Hey, come on.
The goods are on display.

723
00:42:25,001 --> 00:42:26,795
Wait for me, buddy.

724
00:42:56,324 --> 00:42:59,035
There's Fumiko-san.
The one you saw me with.

725
00:42:59,119 --> 00:43:00,912
- Yeah. The little one in pink.
- Yeah, that's the one.

726
00:43:04,791 --> 00:43:06,793
You're not going over there and say hello?

727
00:43:06,835 --> 00:43:10,005
What, in public?
A Matsubayashi girl? Are you nuts?

728
00:43:10,046 --> 00:43:12,424
Well, you take her to the officers‘ club.

729
00:43:12,507 --> 00:43:14,384
Well, that's for Americans.

730
00:43:14,467 --> 00:43:17,512
Thought I could sneak her in there
without her being recognized.

731
00:43:17,971 --> 00:43:20,015
What happens if they catch them?

732
00:43:20,098 --> 00:43:21,766
Immediate dismissal.

733
00:43:21,850 --> 00:43:23,518
- No fooling?
- Yeah.

734
00:43:23,560 --> 00:43:26,396
No Matsubayashi girl
is allowed to have dates of any kind.

735
00:43:27,063 --> 00:43:28,857
You were dating her, you.

736
00:43:29,190 --> 00:43:31,234
Yeah, well, I'm different.

737
00:43:32,360 --> 00:43:33,486
Oh, get out of here.

738
00:43:33,528 --> 00:43:35,864
Well, like I told President Truman,

739
00:43:35,947 --> 00:43:39,075
"Harry, you was wrong
when you sold the Marines short."

740
00:43:39,159 --> 00:43:41,036
See, I hate to be stuffy about this, son,

741
00:43:41,119 --> 00:43:42,871
but you Air Force men
just wouldn't understand.

742
00:43:42,912 --> 00:43:44,122
Lord!

743
00:43:44,748 --> 00:43:48,209
- Well, the Marines have got l’amour.
- Oh, Lord.

744
00:43:48,251 --> 00:43:50,295
And these girls, they got fame and wealth

745
00:43:50,378 --> 00:43:51,880
and bright lights.

746
00:43:52,505 --> 00:43:53,548
But they ain't got l’amour.

747
00:43:53,632 --> 00:43:55,425
-well, you got l’amour, haven't you?
- Yeah, yeah.

748
00:44:04,434 --> 00:44:06,227
What's going on there now?

749
00:44:06,311 --> 00:44:08,104
-Hana-ogi's coming.
- Who?

750
00:44:08,188 --> 00:44:10,690
Hana-ogi. She's the top, number one.

751
00:44:14,402 --> 00:44:16,071
Come on. Let's go.

752
00:44:37,550 --> 00:44:39,511
Well, how come she's dressed like that?

753
00:44:39,594 --> 00:44:42,222
Well, the tall ones play men's parts, mostly.

754
00:44:42,847 --> 00:44:44,516
They play women's parts, too.

755
00:44:44,974 --> 00:44:46,476
How do you do?

756
00:44:52,607 --> 00:44:55,110
What do you say let's see the show?

757
00:44:56,111 --> 00:44:57,612
Well, come on, Ace.

758
00:47:35,353 --> 00:47:37,564
- Hmm?
- I say, do you follow the plot?

759
00:47:38,857 --> 00:47:40,483
Yeah, nothing wrong with the plot.

760
00:50:46,169 --> 00:50:48,463
Listen, are you sure
they're coming back this way?

761
00:50:48,546 --> 00:50:50,882
Just keep yourself in check, son.

762
00:50:52,300 --> 00:50:55,636
Am I nuts, or is she
