between the rocks?

1264
01:28:44,236 --> 01:28:45,738
Yeah.

1265
01:28:45,821 --> 01:28:48,907
That is a Shinto sign
showing they are married.

1266
01:28:49,325 --> 01:28:50,659
What, the rocks?

1267
01:28:50,743 --> 01:28:53,287
Yes.
They've been together so long,

1268
01:28:53,370 --> 01:28:55,706
our people thought
it was time they should get married.

1269
01:28:56,457 --> 01:28:58,459
They look well
together, don't you think?

1270
01:28:58,542 --> 01:29:01,086
Yeah, they make
a handsome-looking couple.

1271
01:29:01,754 --> 01:29:03,672
Do you like my country?

1272
01:29:03,756 --> 01:29:06,258
Yeah. Was all these...
All these funny things here before

1273
01:29:06,300 --> 01:29:07,801
when I came to Japan?

1274
01:29:07,885 --> 01:29:09,094
Yes.

1275
01:29:19,772 --> 01:29:20,939
Well, hello.

1276
01:29:21,023 --> 01:29:23,108
Hello there, Double Ugly.
How are you?

1277
01:29:23,150 --> 01:29:25,235
To what do we
owe the honor of this visit?

1278
01:29:25,861 --> 01:29:30,115
Laundry. Gonna put down
the dirties and pick up the cleans.

1279
01:29:34,286 --> 01:29:36,413
I hope you know
what you're doing.

1280
01:29:37,122 --> 01:29:38,540
This came in
the office this morning.

1281
01:29:38,624 --> 01:29:39,708
Thought you might
like to see it.

1282
01:29:40,250 --> 01:29:43,712
"This is a routine reminder
of the recent orders issued by Camp Kobe."

1283
01:29:43,796 --> 01:29:47,174
Quote, "Any public display,
whatever, of affection

1284
01:29:47,257 --> 01:29:50,761
"for a Japanese national
by a member of this command is forbidden.

1285
01:29:50,803 --> 01:29:53,639
"Officers should not even
appear on public streets

1286
01:29:53,722 --> 01:29:57,142
"accompanied by indigenous
female personnel." Unquote.

1287
01:29:57,226 --> 01:29:58,352
Hooray for Christmas.

1288
01:29:58,727 --> 01:30:01,188
Come on, Ace, this is
serious. Everybody got one of these things.

1289
01:30:01,647 --> 01:30:05,275
Oh, listen, fool, Hana-ogi and I are
just as careful as we can be.

1290
01:30:05,567 --> 01:30:08,737
We never go anyplace where we're gonna be
seen by anybody that matters.

1291
01:30:09,154 --> 01:30:11,657
We don't even walk
down the same street.

1292
01:30:12,825 --> 01:30:14,993
We just go out
in the country and fool around.

1293
01:30:16,203 --> 01:30:18,580
See, listen, you never been to the
country around here, have you?

1294
01:30:19,998 --> 01:30:22,918
Awful pretty country around here.
I mean it.

1295
01:30:23,877 --> 01:30:25,504
You know what
I saw yesterday?

1296
01:30:25,587 --> 01:30:28,173
I saw two rocks
that just got married.

1297
01:30:28,590 --> 01:30:29,633
You what?

1298
01:30:29,675 --> 01:30:31,844
I saw two rocks
that got married.

1299
01:30:31,885 --> 01:30:33,679
And they looked very
happy together, too.

1300
01:30:34,012 --> 01:30:35,347
Oh, I'll bet they did.

1301
01:30:35,597 --> 01:30:36,807
Oh, they did.

1302
01:30:37,683 --> 01:30:40,811
If you gonna be smart,
I'll tell you what you do.

1303
01:30:41,395 --> 01:30:43,730
You get your little shoes shined,
you go out tonight,

1304
01:30:43,814 --> 01:30:46,316
'cause tonight is
gonna be Tanabata.

1305
01:30:47,693 --> 01:30:49,695
Okay, what's Tanabata?

1306
01:30:50,654 --> 01:30:52,990
You mean you're gonna
sit there with your bare face hanging out

1307
01:30:53,031 --> 01:30:54,700
and tell me
you don't know what Tanabata is?

1308
01:30:54,783 --> 01:30:55,784
Yeah.

1309
01:30:56,493 --> 01:30:58,162
Well, my word, boy.

1310
01:30:58,203 --> 01:31:01,206
I'm ashamed of you. I thought
everybody knew what Tanabata was.

1311
01:31:01,707 --> 01:31:04,209
Tanabata is
the night of love.

1312
01:31:04,418 --> 01:31:06,879
You told me
all about it one time.

1313
01:31:06,962 --> 01:31:08,964
You were telling me
about Harry Truman

1314
01:31:09,047 --> 01:31:11,300
and New York Yankees
and sex

1315
01:31:12,468 --> 01:31:14,928
and New York Yankees
and Harry Truman and sex.

1316
01:31:15,012 --> 01:31:16,555
And I'll see you...

1317
01:31:20,058 --> 01:31:21,059
Sex!

1318
01:31:34,781 --> 01:31:37,534
What have I done
to deserve such happiness?

1319
01:31:38,410 --> 01:31:41,914
I have seen this night of
Tanabata come and go many times,

1320
01:31:43,999 --> 01:31:47,794
but never before
have I understood what it meant.

1321
01:31:49,254 --> 01:31:50,797
Tanabata.

1322
01:31:52,007 --> 01:31:55,135
Oh, my heart is so
full of love for you.

1323
01:32:39,096 --> 01:32:40,973
- Miss Webster?
- Yes?

1324
01:32:41,390 --> 01:32:43,517
Nakamura-san gets your note.

1325
01:32:43,600 --> 01:32:44,851
Here is reply.

1326
01:32:44,935 --> 01:32:45,936
Thank you.

1327
01:32:45,978 --> 01:32:49,523
He wishes if you will have
dinner with him and his guests.

1328
01:32:49,606 --> 01:32:51,108
Thank you very much.

1329
01:33:21,430 --> 01:33:26,268
They have a rather
pleasant garden here, Miss Webster.

1330
01:33:28,186 --> 01:33:29,187
Would you like to see it?

1331
01:33:29,938 --> 01:33:31,565
Yes, I think I would.

1332
01:33:56,381 --> 01:33:57,716
How beautiful.

1333
01:34:06,933 --> 01:34:09,895
What are you
really afraid of, Miss Webster?

1334
01:34:09,978 --> 01:34:12,439
You don't think
it would enter Major Gruver's mind

1335
01:34:12,522 --> 01:34:15,567
to marry a Japanese girl?

1336
01:34:17,653 --> 01:34:18,904
I don't know.

1337
01:34:19,780 --> 01:34:22,199
Then permit me
to reassure you.

1338
01:34:22,741 --> 01:34:24,701
I think Major Gruver
is brave

1339
01:34:24,743 --> 01:34:28,121
but not brave enough
to face the censure

1340
01:34:28,205 --> 01:34:30,749
that would result
from such a marriage.

1341
01:34:31,124 --> 01:34:34,586
As for our famous,
honored Hana-ogi,

1342
01:34:35,295 --> 01:34:37,631
there are many Japanese,

1343
01:34:37,714 --> 01:34:39,091
most of them, in fact,

1344
01:34:39,591 --> 01:34:43,303
who look upon marriage
to an occidental with as much distaste

1345
01:34:43,387 --> 01:34:46,306
as your people do
to one of us.

1346
01:34:47,182 --> 01:34:49,601
I do not feel that way.

1347
01:34:50,018 --> 01:34:51,728
But, then,
I have had the privilege

1348
01:34:51,770 --> 01:34:53,647
of traveling
in your country

1349
01:34:53,730 --> 01:34:56,566
and knowing some
great people there.

1350
01:34:57,442 --> 01:35:01,738
And I am especially
conscious at this moment

1351
01:35:01,780 --> 01:35:05,701
that beauty
is not confined to any one race.

1352
01:35:10,205 --> 01:35:12,416
Do not turn away,
Miss Webster.

1353
01:35:12,749 --> 01:35:17,879
I am not necessarily
making love to you.

1354
01:35:21,216 --> 01:35:23,051
I am only stating a very

1355
01:35:24,553 --> 01:35:26,221
obvious fact.

1356
01:35:28,348 --> 01:35:30,642
May I see you again,
Miss Webster,

1357
01:35:31,268 --> 01:35:34,813
and acquaint you
with more Japan?

1358
01:35:36,148 --> 01:35:37,524
Of course.

1359
01:35:37,983 --> 01:35:40,110
I need to know more,
much more,

1360
01:35:41,445 --> 01:35:42,821
about everything.

1361
01:36:03,592 --> 01:36:05,510
There she is.

1362
01:36:07,554 --> 01:36:09,139
Hello, honey.

1363
01:36:21,693 --> 01:36:23,111
Are you tired?

1364
01:36:25,906 --> 01:36:29,493
No, TIM...
TIM been lying here

1365
01:36:29,534 --> 01:36:31,369
thinking about myself.

1366
01:36:32,204 --> 01:36:34,164
You know,
I can't believe I'm really here.

1367
01:36:35,791 --> 01:36:37,626
It's hard to believe that...

1368
01:36:37,709 --> 01:36:41,213
You know, it's hard
to believe me being the same Lloyd Gruver

1369
01:36:41,254 --> 01:36:44,049
that came over from Korea
just a little bit ago.

1370
01:36:47,177 --> 01:36:48,637
You know, I been thinking

1371
01:36:49,471 --> 01:36:50,889
that all my life

1372
01:36:51,515 --> 01:36:53,141
I been so busy

1373
01:36:54,142 --> 01:36:57,312
snapping to,
and giving orders, and taking orders,

1374
01:36:57,395 --> 01:37:00,732
and being a general’s son,
and doing the job

1375
01:37:02,234 --> 01:37:06,071
and all that,
I just never took time to sit right down

1376
01:37:08,031 --> 01:37:12,077
and, you know, think about
what my reason for living is.

1377
01:37:15,080 --> 01:37:17,999
And I been spending
some afternoons here just

1378
01:37:19,292 --> 01:37:20,919
being peaceful

1379
01:37:22,087 --> 01:37:24,047
and easy and thinking.

1380
01:37:26,550 --> 01:37:28,927
And I believe
for the first time,

1381
01:37:31,263 --> 01:37:35,350
I'm just beginning
to understand

1382
01:37:35,433 --> 01:37:37,185
what it's all about,

1383
01:37:38,854 --> 01:37:41,106
what I really am,
what I really want.

1384
01:37:42,691 --> 01:37:44,234
It's a nice feeling.

1385
01:37:54,119 --> 01:37:55,453
Yeah, come on in.

1386
01:37:56,663 --> 01:37:59,332
Ace, excuse me.
I hate to bother you.

1387
01:37:59,416 --> 01:38:01,126
TIM got the news.

1388
01:38:01,209 --> 01:38:02,627
You got what news?

1389
01:38:02,961 --> 01:38:04,212
I'm getting shipped back.

1390
01:38:05,547 --> 01:38:07,007
You being shipped
back where?

1391
01:38:07,424 --> 01:38:08,758
Stateside.

1392
01:38:09,134 --> 01:38:10,969
I've been reassigned
to a new duty station.

1393
01:38:11,761 --> 01:38:14,306
Well...

1394
01:38:16,057 --> 01:38:17,517
Did you tell Katsumi yet?

1395
01:38:17,601 --> 01:38:18,727
No.

1396
01:38:18,810 --> 01:38:21,354
All right. Well, don't tell her, because
maybe we can work something out.

1397
01:38:21,813 --> 01:38:24,316
What reason did
he give you for it?

1398
01:38:25,025 --> 01:38:27,736
No reason.
I know what it is.

1399
01:38:28,653 --> 01:38:31,698
Every guy on that list
is married to a Japanese girl.

1400
01:38:36,912 --> 01:38:39,831
I'm sorry, Major.
There's nothing you can do.

1401
01:38:43,335 --> 01:38:46,630
We're sending Kelly
to the States Thursday, and that's that.

1402
01:38:49,466 --> 01:38:51,217
Well, what about
his wife, Colonel?

1403
01:38:52,344 --> 01:38:53,637
Well, she stays here.

1404
01:38:55,263 --> 01:38:57,849
He knew he couldn't take her back with
him when he married her.

1405
01:38:57,891 --> 01:38:58,892
Mmm-hmm.

1406
01:38:59,351 --> 01:39:00,518
Didn't you?

1407
01:39:00,602 --> 01:39:01,811
That's right.

1408
01:39:03,521 --> 01:39:05,607
Well, you'd be busting up
his home then, you know.

1409
01:39:05,899 --> 01:39:07,776
I'm not busting up anything.

1410
01:39:10,028 --> 01:39:14,407
Oh, I admit Kelly's
been a pain in my side for quite a while now.

1411
01:39:14,532 --> 01:39:15,951
Well, could you tell me

1412
01:39:16,034 --> 01:39:19,120
why he didn't have
the privilege of extending his tour of duty?

1413
01:39:19,204 --> 01:39:20,705
Don't ask me, Major.

1414
01:39:21,289 --> 01:39:23,667
There are lots of reasons
for these things.

1415
01:39:24,793 --> 01:39:27,337
Anyway, it is an order.

1416
01:39:27,879 --> 01:39:29,547
And there's nothing
you can do about it

1417
01:39:30,590 --> 01:39:32,717
even if you are
a four-star general’s son.

1418
01:39:34,678 --> 01:39:35,887
Yeah, well...

1419
01:39:38,974 --> 01:39:42,227
Would it make any difference
if I told you my wife's going to have a baby?

1420
01:39:46,064 --> 01:39:47,691
Well, that's tough,
I admit.

1421
01:39:50,652 --> 01:39:51,987
Colonel, under these circumstances,

1422
01:39:52,070 --> 01:39:54,239
don't you think
that you'd be able to

1423
01:39:55,073 --> 01:39:57,242
postpone this
for a little while?

1424
01:39:58,076 --> 01:40:00,161
Maybe I could be
transferred back to Korea.

1425
01:40:01,287 --> 01:40:03,164
No, you're going home.

1426
01:40:05,709 --> 01:40:08,294
All the boys
on this list, going home.

1427
01:40:10,255 --> 01:40:11,256
Where is your home?

1428
01:40:12,424 --> 01:40:13,842
That house by the canal.

1429
01:40:15,218 --> 01:40:16,344
I mean your real home.

1430
01:40:16,886 --> 01:40:18,263
That house by the canal.

1431
01:40:18,304 --> 01:40:19,931
Yeah, all right.

1432
01:40:22,267 --> 01:40:25,729
I've taken all the insubordination
from you I intend to.

1433
01:40:26,938 --> 01:40:29,107
Now, you listen
to me, wise guy,

1434
01:40:29,899 --> 01:40:33,945
that house by the canal
is off-limits from now on.

1435
01:40:35,739 --> 01:40:37,699
Whole street's off-limits.

1436
01:40:38,450 --> 01:40:39,826
You want a court-martial?

1437
01:40:41,411 --> 01:40:42,996
That mean I could
stay in Japan?

1438
01:40:43,079 --> 01:40:44,122
Come on, Kel.

1439
01:40:44,164 --> 01:40:45,540
You're shipping out
of here on Thursday.

1440
01:40:45,623 --> 01:40:47,167
And don't you
try to help him.

1441
01:40:50,378 --> 01:40:52,464
You remember that
house by the canal

1442
01:40:53,048 --> 01:40:55,300
is off-limits to all personnel.

1443
01:40:57,552 --> 01:40:59,220
Would you tell me,
Colonel, just exactly

1444
01:40:59,304 --> 01:41:01,473
what you mean
by that last remark?

1445
01:41:01,848 --> 01:41:04,142
Well, that's all
I'm prepared to say at the minute,

1446
01:41:05,226 --> 01:41:06,394
except you watch your step.

1447
01:41:12,817 --> 01:41:15,612
So, I don't know
what else to say to you, General.

1448
01:41:15,653 --> 01:41:17,155
I've known this boy
a long time,

1449
01:41:17,197 --> 01:41:20,075
and if he has to go back without
Katsumi, he's gonna be in trouble.

1450
01:41:20,700 --> 01:41:21,701
And...

1451
01:41:22,243 --> 01:41:24,329
Well, I mean,
that's about it. That's it.

1452
01:41:24,996 --> 01:41:26,247
What about his wife?

1453
01:41:26,873 --> 01:41:28,875
-I don't know.
- And the baby?

1454
01:41:31,419 --> 01:41:34,089
So it comes down to
the fact that the Army lets them get married

1455
01:41:34,172 --> 01:41:36,007
and then forces
them to desert their wives and babies.

1456
01:41:36,674 --> 01:41:38,510
That's not fair, Eileen.

1457
01:41:39,302 --> 01:41:42,847
A boy away from home
for the first time, lonesome,

1458
01:41:42,931 --> 01:41:45,517
often falls in love
with the first girl he touches.

1459
01:41:45,600 --> 01:41:47,685
In most cases,
with a girl from the streets.

1460
01:41:48,895 --> 01:41:50,647
It's up to the service
in some measure

1461
01:41:50,688 --> 01:41:52,899
to be fathers
and mothers to these boys

1462
01:41:55,026 --> 01:41:57,695
and try to head off
these marriages.

1463
01:41:58,113 --> 01:42:00,615
But after they're married
why should they be sent home?

1464
01:42:00,698 --> 01:42:03,493
The man's being transferred
to a new duty station, Eileen,

1465
01:42:03,535 --> 01:42:04,702
along with many others.

1466
01:42:04,744 --> 01:42:07,372
Now, don't ask me
the reasons for changes of duty.

1467
01:42:07,831 --> 01:42:09,374
There are thousands of them.

1468
01:42:09,457 --> 01:42:11,876
But Lloyd said
that most of the men on this particular list

1469
01:42:11,918 --> 01:42:13,545
are married to Japanese girls.

1470
01:42:13,586 --> 01:42:15,213
That can't be just
a coincidence, Father.

1471
01:42:15,296 --> 01:42:16,548
Why not?
It could easily be.

1472
01:42:16,631 --> 01:42:18,716
There have been
lots of marriages.

1473
01:42:18,800 --> 01:42:21,010
Frankly, with some
of these men,

1474
01:42:21,302 --> 01:42:24,055
I think they might
welcome the transfer.

1475
01:42:24,514 --> 01:42:25,849
Why is that, sir?

1476
01:42:26,432 --> 01:42:30,019
There have been unfortunate
aftermaths to many of these marriages.

1477
01:42:30,061 --> 01:42:32,063
Recriminations, regrets.

1478
01:42:33,857 --> 01:42:36,234
A boy gets married
impulsively, then feels caught,

1479
01:42:36,317 --> 01:42:38,611
doesn't know how to get out of
it, doesn't know what to do.

1480
01:42:38,695 --> 01:42:41,239
Change of duty
gives them both a chance to think it over.

1481
01:42:41,322 --> 01:42:42,490
To cool off.

1482
01:42:43,741 --> 01:42:45,785
Now, I don't mean to
imply that that's the reason

1483
01:42:45,869 --> 01:42:48,037
these men are being
transferred, but...

1484
01:42:48,413 --> 01:42:49,747
Well...

1485
01:42:51,374 --> 01:42:53,001
The whole thing's

1486
01:42:53,960 --> 01:42:55,336
a messy business.

1487
01:42:56,963 --> 01:43:00,592
General Webster, there is no regret in the
case of Kelly and Katsumi.

1488
01:43:01,676 --> 01:43:03,595
You can have
my word on that.

1489
01:43:04,012 --> 01:43:05,013
Lloyd,

1490
01:43:06,014 --> 01:43:08,099
three officers
came to me today

1491
01:43:08,183 --> 01:43:10,226
with identical requests
for their men.

1492
01:43:10,727 --> 01:43:12,520
It's not our policy
to interfere with decisions

1493
01:43:12,604 --> 01:43:14,856
made by immediate
commanding officers.

1494
01:43:14,939 --> 01:43:17,567
The basic structure
of the whole military service would collapse

1495
01:43:17,609 --> 01:43:19,527
if we started doing
things like that.

1496
01:43:21,070 --> 01:43:23,198
Your father would
understand that, even if you don't.

1497
01:43:24,782 --> 01:43:27,118
Are you going to
ask me to make an exception of Kelly

1498
01:43:27,160 --> 01:43:28,786
when I've refused
these other men?

1499
01:43:32,123 --> 01:43:34,459
I am going to ask you
to do that, sir.

1500
01:43:36,461 --> 01:43:39,255
You made an exception of me
when you brought me from Korea.

1501
01:43:42,300 --> 01:43:45,261
I'm afraid
it's a hopeless situation, Lloyd.

1502
01:43:50,725 --> 01:43:51,726
Well...

1503
01:43:54,103 --> 01:43:55,939
That's the end of Joe Kelly.

1504
01:43:57,523 --> 01:44:00,693
You told me yourself
that Kelly's past record was against him.

1505
01:44:00,777 --> 01:44:02,570
I couldn't even use that,
don't you see?

1506
01:44:02,654 --> 01:44:05,114
Why does this mean
so much to you, Lloyd?

1507
01:44:07,825 --> 01:44:11,537
Kelly's from my outfit, Mrs. Webster.
I was his best man.

1508
01:44:12,163 --> 01:44:14,916
And I'm planning to marry
a Japanese girl myself.

1509
01:44:19,754 --> 01:44:21,839
Come into the other room, Eileen.

1510
01:44:21,923 --> 01:44:24,050
This is something
for your father to handle.

1511
01:44:24,801 --> 01:44:28,513
No, Mrs. Webster, I don't think it's
anything for anybody to handle.

1512
01:44:35,019 --> 01:44:36,437
I'm sorry, Eileen.

1513
01:44:41,734 --> 01:44:42,986
Mrs. Webster.

1514
01:44:43,611 --> 01:44:45,113
Good afternoon, y'all.

1515
01:44:51,536 --> 01:44:55,373
I don't think I'll ever love anyone
again as much as I love Lloyd.

1516
01:44:56,749 --> 01:44:58,876
But I'll tell you something
that's rather ironic.

1517
01:45:00,586 --> 01:45:03,673
I once asked Lloyd
if he ever felt like grabbing me

1518
01:45:04,048 --> 01:45:06,426
and hauling me off
to a shack somewhere.

1519
01:45:08,386 --> 01:45:10,138
That's just what
he's done, isn't it?

1520
01:45:10,972 --> 01:45:12,390
Only it's with somebody else.

1521
01:45:13,641 --> 01:45:15,560
Don't go out, Eileen.

1522
01:45:15,601 --> 01:45:16,769
Stay and talk.

1523
01:45:16,853 --> 01:45:18,229
I'm sorry, Mother.

1524
01:45:18,313 --> 01:45:20,732
There's only one person
I'd like to talk to at the moment,

1525
01:45:21,232 --> 01:45:23,401
and oddly enough,
he's Japanese.

1526
01:45:28,239 --> 01:45:29,907
Ace, I've been
waiting for you.

1527
01:45:29,991 --> 01:45:31,409
Hey, Kelly, listen.

1528
01:45:31,868 --> 01:45:34,954
I just came from
General Webster's house

1529
01:45:35,038 --> 01:45:36,581
and there's a whole
big mess there.

1530
01:45:36,664 --> 01:45:37,915
-No good, huh?
- No.

1531
01:45:38,416 --> 01:45:40,918
He didn't...
He didn't go for it.

1532
01:45:41,794 --> 01:45:44,422
Matter of fact,
I think I even messed it up a little.

1533
01:45:46,132 --> 01:45:47,633
That figures.

1534
01:45:48,426 --> 01:45:50,011
Did you tell
Katsumi yet?

1535
01:45:50,094 --> 01:45:51,137
No.

1536
01:45:51,929 --> 01:45:53,639
I'm chickening out fast.

1537
01:45:54,557 --> 01:45:57,727
Besides, she's got her heart set on
something she planned for us tonight.

1538
01:45:58,186 --> 01:45:59,896
Wants us both to take
the train to Osaka

1539
01:45:59,937 --> 01:46:02,106
and meet the girls
at the puppet show.

1540
01:46:03,775 --> 01:46:05,068
Why Spoil it?

1541
01:46:07,653 --> 01:46:09,989
Maybe I'll tell
her late tonight when we're alone.

1542
01:46:13,076 --> 01:46:16,162
Kelly, don't give up on it.
I think there's gonna be a way out of it.

1543
01:46:16,245 --> 01:46:17,246
- There's got to be.
- You think so?

1544
01:46:17,288 --> 01:46:18,664
- Yes, I do.
-I don't.

1545
01:46:21,125 --> 01:46:22,460
- I'll see you, Ace.
- Hi, hon.

1546
01:46:22,502 --> 01:46:23,503
Kelly-san.

1547
01:46:25,088 --> 01:46:27,423
Hey, tell Katsumi
we'll be there with bells.

1548
01:46:29,050 --> 01:46:30,635
Were you able to help?

1549
01:46:34,263 --> 01:46:35,890
No. I wasn't.

1550
01:46:35,973 --> 01:46:37,475
How terrible.

1551
01:46:41,604 --> 01:46:42,980
I know this is hard, honey.

1552
01:46:43,022 --> 01:46:45,316
It's hard,
but it's not gonna last long.

1553
01:46:45,358 --> 01:46:49,112
I mean, the Army's got to change that
law next year or the next one.

1554
01:46:50,113 --> 01:46:53,116
I mean, it just has to be.
I'm sure of it.

1555
01:46:55,118 --> 01:46:57,161
And, as a matter of fact,

1556
01:46:57,203 --> 01:46:59,956
I'm so sure of it
that I went downtown today

1557
01:46:59,997 --> 01:47:02,667
and I signed
some papers here

1558
01:47:02,708 --> 01:47:05,044
that mean that you and I
are gonna get married.

1559
01:47:08,131 --> 01:47:09,298
What's the matter?

1560
01:47:09,340 --> 01:47:11,008
We never spoke of marriage.

1561
01:47:11,926 --> 01:47:13,970
I know we didn't, darling.

1562
01:47:14,887 --> 01:47:19,267
I know we didn't.
I been going round and round with that

1563
01:47:19,350 --> 01:47:21,352
every day for a long time.

1564
01:47:22,311 --> 01:47:25,565
And I didn't feel I could
speak about it until now.

1565
01:47:27,024 --> 01:47:28,359
Now I can.

1566
01:47:30,278 --> 01:47:33,739
Now, of course,
I won't be able to take you back to America,

1567
01:47:33,823 --> 01:47:36,534
but they're bound to change
that ridiculous law soon.

1568
01:47:37,994 --> 01:47:40,538
And until then,
I'm gonna stay here with you.

1569
01:47:42,874 --> 01:47:45,960
I'm not stuck in the Air Force.
I can resign.

1570
01:47:46,043 --> 01:47:49,213
Of course,
I'm not trained to do anything else,

1571
01:47:50,047 --> 01:47:51,174
but I'd find something.

1572
01:47:52,717 --> 01:47:54,844
We never spoke of marriage.

1573
01:47:56,387 --> 01:47:59,891
I know we didn't, darling,
but we're speaking of it now.

1574
01:48:07,523 --> 01:48:10,359
Do you remember
the first night we talked?

1575
01:48:11,068 --> 01:48:14,947
I said there would
be danger of weakness when it is over.

1576
01:48:18,242 --> 01:48:20,661
Over?
What are you talking about?

1577
01:48:24,165 --> 01:48:27,460
I am tempted.
With you, I could become a woman.

1578
01:48:28,419 --> 01:48:31,881
And a mother.
And I could love you.

1579
01:48:34,091 --> 01:48:35,510
That's right.

1580
01:48:36,093 --> 01:48:38,721
Do you think I haven't
thought about it?

1581
01:48:39,222 --> 01:48:42,266
Do you think
I want to become a lonely old woman

1582
01:48:42,308 --> 01:48:45,937
who teaches dancing,
now that I have known you?

1583
01:48:48,356 --> 01:48:50,024
But it is no good.

1584
01:48:51,150 --> 01:48:52,485
You must know it, too.

1585
01:48:52,902 --> 01:48:56,322
No, no. I don't know
anything of the kind.

1586
01:48:57,990 --> 01:49:00,660
The way you talk about
leaving the Air Force,

1587
01:49:01,786 --> 01:49:04,372
finding some pitiful
way of earning living

1588
01:49:04,455 --> 01:49:06,999
just to be here with
your Japanese wife.

1589
01:49:07,333 --> 01:49:09,335
Now, wait a minute.
Wait a minute.

1590
01:49:12,755 --> 01:49:15,841
I think we're too far
in this thing to be talking like that.

1591
01:49:17,760 --> 01:49:20,471
Matsubayashi has been
kind to me, Lloyd.

1592
01:49:22,014 --> 01:49:23,975
I am obligated to them.

1593
01:49:24,433 --> 01:49:28,145
No, you ain't.
You... No, no. You obligated to me.

1594
01:49:29,689 --> 01:49:31,315
They are my life.

1595
01:49:31,941 --> 01:49:34,819
I will bring shame
to them, disgrace.

1596
01:49:35,820 --> 01:49:37,989
Lloyd, you know
what I mean?

1597
01:49:38,072 --> 01:49:41,659
Yeah, I think
I'm beginning to know what you mean.

1598
01:49:41,701 --> 01:49:45,580
I think you mean you simply don't love me
enough to go on through with it.

1599
01:49:45,663 --> 01:49:47,873
That's what you mean,
don't you?

1600
01:49:47,957 --> 01:49:50,376
Why don't you
just come on out and say it?

1601
01:49:50,459 --> 01:49:52,336
It is not what I mean.

1602
01:49:57,258 --> 01:49:59,677
I'm leaving for Tokyo
in six days.

1603
01:50:00,636 --> 01:50:03,014
Matsubayashi are sending me.

1604
01:50:03,097 --> 01:50:04,807
You What?

1605
01:50:06,976 --> 01:50:11,147
With another troupe.
They have found out about us.

1606
01:50:12,356 --> 01:50:16,402
Any other girl, they would have
dismissed, but because they like me,

1607
01:50:16,485 --> 01:50:20,823
because they feel I am important
to them, they are being lenient.

1608
01:50:22,199 --> 01:50:24,660
Well, I'm not gonna be
lenient with you.

1609
01:50:25,536 --> 01:50:26,912
I want you to
tell me right now

1610
01:50:26,996 --> 01:50:29,874
why Matsubayashi
means more to you than I do?

1611
01:50:32,877 --> 01:50:35,838
Lloyd, there is something
about myself

1612
01:50:35,880 --> 01:50:37,381
I have not told you.

1613
01:50:38,799 --> 01:50:41,135
I have no right
to marry anyone.

1614
01:50:42,219 --> 01:50:44,221
My father was very poor.

1615
01:50:45,473 --> 01:50:48,059
To save his other children,

1616
01:50:48,142 --> 01:50:50,686
he was forced to sell
one of his daughters.

1617
01:50:52,396 --> 01:50:55,566
The man from the houses
of Yoshiwara came to him.

1618
01:50:57,193 --> 01:50:59,278
Because I was the oldest,

1619
01:51:00,571 --> 01:51:02,907
he agreed I should
go with them.

1620
01:51:04,867 --> 01:51:07,078
Your father sold you?

1621
01:51:08,245 --> 01:51:12,166
Yes, but I was saved
from starting this life

1622
01:51:12,750 --> 01:51:14,960
by my best friend,
Fumiko-san.

1623
01:51:17,588 --> 01:51:20,091
Her father paid
money to free me

1624
01:51:21,676 --> 01:51:24,178
and she brought me
to Matsubayashi.

1625
01:51:27,765 --> 01:51:30,601
There, I not only
earn my living,

1626
01:51:31,977 --> 01:51:34,605
I brought honor
back to my family.

1627
01:51:37,274 --> 01:51:39,735
Matsubayashi has
been kind to me.

1628
01:51:40,569 --> 01:51:42,363
They have trusted me.

1629
01:51:43,948 --> 01:51:45,616
I cannot leave them.

1630
01:51:46,659 --> 01:51:48,619
I cannot marry anyone.

1631
01:51:52,748 --> 01:51:54,875
Don't you understand?

1632
01:52:01,632 --> 01:52:02,883
I don't know.

1633
01:52:04,885 --> 01:52:06,095
I don't know
what to think.

1634
01:52:09,515 --> 01:52:10,599
I'll kill you!

1635
01:52:10,641 --> 01:52:12,101
You ever do
anything like this,

1636
01:52:12,143 --> 01:52:13,519
and I'll kill you,
you understand?

1637
01:52:13,602 --> 01:52:15,688
Get that straight, now!
I'll kill you!

1638
01:52:15,771 --> 01:52:17,940
Wait a minute. Listen.
Just take it easy, now.

1639
01:52:17,982 --> 01:52:19,400
Ace, look at this.

1640
01:52:22,153 --> 01:52:23,904
-It fell out of her bag.
- What is it?

1641
01:52:23,988 --> 01:52:25,823
She was gonna
have it done, too.

1642
01:52:25,865 --> 01:52:28,409
Tomorrow,
by that quack doctor down by the docks.

1643
01:52:28,492 --> 01:52:30,703
- What?
-For 8 bucks, she slashes her eyelids

1644
01:52:30,786 --> 01:52:32,913
and sews them
back up again.

1645
01:52:32,997 --> 01:52:35,124
Lots of these stupid little jerks
have it done.

1646
01:52:35,166 --> 01:52:36,751
She was gonna surprise me.

1647
01:52:37,460 --> 01:52:38,461
Well...

1648
01:52:38,502 --> 01:52:39,670
Then...

1649
01:52:39,754 --> 01:52:43,632
Then I have good eyes.
I fool everybody.

1650
01:52:44,008 --> 01:52:46,886
I look American, like Joe.

1651
01:52:48,012 --> 01:52:53,142
Hana-ogi, will you tell
that stupid dame I love her the way she is?

1652
01:52:53,559 --> 01:52:55,144
I don't want her changed.

1653
01:52:55,186 --> 01:52:57,021
Will you tell her
I love her mouth

1654
01:52:57,062 --> 01:53:00,316
and her nose
and her ears and her eyes

1655
01:53:00,357 --> 01:53:02,109
just the way they are?

1656
01:53:02,193 --> 01:53:05,446
Tell her if she ever does
anything like that, I'll...

1657
01:53:06,197 --> 01:53:07,490
Wait a minute.
Calm down, Kelly.

1658
01:53:07,531 --> 01:53:09,950
I want him
be proud of me.

1659
01:53:10,034 --> 01:53:11,202
Listen, listen. Listen.

1660
01:53:11,452 --> 01:53:13,078
I am sorry.

1661
01:53:13,162 --> 01:53:16,207
Listen, if you want him
to be proud of you, you got to quit this stuff.

1662
01:53:16,290 --> 01:53:17,708
‘Cause you want to be
a good wife, don't you?

1663
01:53:17,750 --> 01:53:19,877
You're making him
very unhappy when you're doing that.

1664
01:53:19,960 --> 01:53:22,213
Now, tell him you're sorry
and you're not going to do it anymore.

1665
01:53:22,254 --> 01:53:23,547
Tell him that.

1666
01:53:23,631 --> 01:53:24,632
Joe...

1667
01:53:26,884 --> 01:53:28,719
I so sorry.

1668
01:53:31,263 --> 01:53:34,225
Okay. Now, we're gonna
forget about that, all right?

1669
01:53:34,850 --> 01:53:36,477
Now, listen.
I came over here tonight,

1670
01:53:36,560 --> 01:53:38,187
I thought we were gonna
have a fish fry.

1671
01:53:38,229 --> 01:53:40,439
We were gonna have some fun right
here, and dancing and yelling,

1672
01:53:40,523 --> 01:53:41,816
and what do I find?

1673
01:53:41,899 --> 01:53:43,400
What's gonna happen to us?

1674
01:53:43,484 --> 01:53:44,527
Puppet show.

1675
01:53:44,568 --> 01:53:46,487
-Yeah, we had a surprise...
- You like?

1676
01:53:46,570 --> 01:53:48,280
Sure, I do.
Been looking forward to it.

1677
01:53:48,823 --> 01:53:51,242
I know everybody tonight.

1678
01:53:51,325 --> 01:53:52,535
Yeah.

1679
01:53:55,579 --> 01:53:56,580
And

1680
01:53:56,997 --> 01:53:58,415
we will be late.

1681
01:54:06,507 --> 01:54:07,550
Look.

1682
01:54:08,259 --> 01:54:12,930
The lover is leaving the city,
walk to the wood.

1683
01:54:50,551 --> 01:54:54,221
Lloyd, don't think
of anything now.

1684
01:54:55,431 --> 01:54:56,974
Watch the play.

1685
01:54:57,808 --> 01:54:59,602
It's a tender story.

1686
01:55:08,110 --> 01:55:11,864
When gong sound,
it is done.

1687
01:55:12,197 --> 01:55:17,119
And then she will
bind her body.

1688
01:55:18,704 --> 01:55:20,122
Bind her body?

1689
01:55:20,164 --> 01:55:23,459
So that she will not fall
in an ugly position

1690
01:55:23,500 --> 01:55:25,669
of dishonor when she dies.

1691
01:55:26,086 --> 01:55:27,171
- When she dies?
- Mmm.

1692
01:55:27,254 --> 01:55:28,589
Yes, shinju.

1693
01:55:46,523 --> 01:55:48,692
It is custom for lovers

1694
01:55:48,776 --> 01:55:52,112
to die together
when they can no longer face life.

1695
01:56:02,998 --> 01:56:05,125
It is so beautiful.

1696
01:56:06,043 --> 01:56:08,879
Beautiful?
They're gonna die, aren't they?

1697
01:56:09,588 --> 01:56:13,968
They will live
in another world on a beautiful lake

1698
01:56:14,551 --> 01:56:16,887
floating always together

1699
01:56:17,680 --> 01:56:19,390
like water lily.

1700
01:56:22,601 --> 01:56:23,727
Sure.

1701
01:57:45,851 --> 01:57:48,896
Kelly-san! Kelly-san!
Kelly-san!

1702
01:57:59,364 --> 01:58:01,658
Something about soldiers
going through the house.

1703
01:58:07,539 --> 01:58:08,707
That's the MPs, boy.

1704
01:58:08,791 --> 01:58:10,542
-What happened? What's wrong?
- Come here, come here.

1705
01:58:10,626 --> 01:58:12,211
- What happened?
- Get in the car.

1706
01:58:15,005 --> 01:58:16,256
Go to Matsubayashi.

1707
01:58:16,340 --> 01:58:18,175
- Please, please tell me. I will not leave.
- I will, I will.

1708
01:58:18,217 --> 01:58:19,676
Now, get in the car.
I'll tell you later.

1709
01:58:19,760 --> 01:58:21,261
Matsubayashi.

1710
01:58:24,014 --> 01:58:25,265
Hey, Ed, look.

1711
01:58:41,532 --> 01:58:42,658
Look at that.

1712
01:58:45,869 --> 01:58:47,371
You're Major Gruver,
aren't you?

1713
01:58:48,163 --> 01:58:49,206
That's right.

1714
01:58:49,289 --> 01:58:50,791
Sorry, Major, you'll have
to come with us.

1715
01:58:50,874 --> 01:58:52,042
General Webster's orders.

1716
01:58:52,209 --> 01:58:54,378
So, what right do
you have to board up this man's house?

1717
01:58:54,419 --> 01:58:55,921
He won't be needing
it anymore, Major.

1718
01:58:56,004 --> 01:58:57,089
He's shipping out Thursday.

1719
01:58:57,214 --> 01:58:58,215
Joe?

1720
01:58:59,174 --> 01:59:00,551
Come on, Major.

1721
01:59:02,719 --> 01:59:04,304
You'll hear from me, Kelly.

1722
01:59:18,777 --> 01:59:20,362
Come on, kid.

1723
01:59:20,404 --> 01:59:24,158
We'll get in through the garden.
I got something to tell you.

1724
01:59:47,389 --> 01:59:48,932
You were seen
in public with her tonight,

1725
01:59:48,974 --> 01:59:51,101
violating the orders
of the area.

1726
01:59:51,143 --> 01:59:53,353
This has given
me the right to put you under arrest.

1727
01:59:54,730 --> 01:59:57,065
And, for your own sake,
I think I'd better do it.

1728
01:59:58,233 --> 01:59:59,234
Well,

1729
01:59:59,776 --> 02:00:01,236
you have anything to say?

1730
02:00:03,739 --> 02:00:06,867
Well, just as soon I'm out of this,
I'm going to be married,

1731
02:00:06,950 --> 02:00:08,368
and have a house of my own.

1732
02:00:10,871 --> 02:00:12,414
I'm afraid not.

1733
02:00:12,873 --> 02:00:15,167
I'm sorry, Lloyd,
but it's all settled.

1734
02:00:15,250 --> 02:00:18,670
The supervisor of the Matsubayashi
came to see me tonight.

1735
02:00:19,171 --> 02:00:21,757
The girl goes
to Tokyo, and you fly to Randolph Field,

1736
02:00:22,299 --> 02:00:23,383
day after tomorrow.

1737
02:00:24,301 --> 02:00:25,844
Here are your orders.

1738
02:00:27,221 --> 02:00:29,348
Until that time,
you're under house arrest.

1739
02:00:31,266 --> 02:00:34,686
You're not to leave
your quarters until further notice.

1740
02:00:40,150 --> 02:00:43,320
I'm doing this because I feel you're not
responsible at the moment, Lloyd.

1741
02:00:43,403 --> 02:00:45,822
After all, I've known
your father for years.

1742
02:00:52,037 --> 02:00:53,664
Well, that's all.

1743
02:01:29,366 --> 02:01:30,450
Mike...

1744
02:01:31,576 --> 02:01:32,703
Did you see her?

1745
02:01:32,786 --> 02:01:34,162
No, Ace. I couldn't even get
near the place.

1746
02:01:34,204 --> 02:01:35,247
They've really clamped down.

1747
02:01:35,330 --> 02:01:37,541
I went to the stage
door and I couldn't even see Fumiko-san.

1748
02:01:37,624 --> 02:01:40,294
Well, listen, I've got to see her.
I'm being shipped out of here tomorrow.

1749
02:01:40,669 --> 02:01:42,087
Major Gruver?

1750
02:01:42,170 --> 02:01:43,297
What is it?

1751
02:01:43,380 --> 02:01:44,548
Would you do
something for us?

1752
02:01:44,589 --> 02:01:45,841
What do you want?

1753
02:01:46,633 --> 02:01:48,218
Airman Kelly's disappeared.

1754
02:01:48,302 --> 02:01:51,305
No, that's impossible.
I was with him just last night.

1755
02:01:51,388 --> 02:01:52,431
We know.

1756
02:01:52,514 --> 02:01:53,974
He was scheduled to fly out
in a couple days.

1757
02:01:54,057 --> 02:01:57,602
But a special plane came through, and
Colonel Crawford told us to get him on it.

1758
02:01:57,686 --> 02:02:00,105
I took him to
the airport at 12:50.

1759
02:02:00,188 --> 02:02:03,025
When the plane took off,
Kelly wasn't on it.

1760
02:02:03,066 --> 02:02:04,401
Figured you might
know where he is.

1761
02:02:04,443 --> 02:02:07,821
How should I know where he is?
His house has been boarded up, hasn't it?

1762
02:02:07,904 --> 02:02:10,741
We know.
Neighbors won't talk to us.

1763
02:02:10,824 --> 02:02:12,492
We figure maybe
they're hiding him.

1764
02:02:13,076 --> 02:02:15,620
They'll talk with you, Major.
Would you help us?

1765
02:02:16,538 --> 02:02:19,249
Well, would you give
me one good reason why I should?

1766
02:02:21,335 --> 02:02:23,211
We figured we'd
give him a break.

1767
02:02:23,253 --> 02:02:24,921
We haven't reported
him as yet.

1768
02:02:24,963 --> 02:02:27,049
We could get him
on another plane.

1769
02:02:27,090 --> 02:02:29,134
We might not have
to turn him in for desertion.

1770
02:02:31,303 --> 02:02:33,055
- Desertion?
-Yes, sir.

1771
02:02:36,933 --> 02:02:38,101
Well...

1772
02:02:39,811 --> 02:02:41,438
I'll go with
you in a minute.

1773
02:02:41,980 --> 02:02:43,148
Major?

1774
02:02:43,607 --> 02:02:46,109
The neighbors won't
talk if they see an MP.

1775
02:02:46,151 --> 02:02:47,277
I'll go with him.

1776
02:02:47,361 --> 02:02:48,904
Thank you, sir.

1777
02:03:49,506 --> 02:03:50,757
Kelly?

1778
02:03:54,094 --> 02:03:55,679
Kelly, Gruver out here.

1779
02:03:58,181 --> 02:03:59,516
I think he's in there.

1780
02:04:01,768 --> 02:04:02,853
Kelly?

1781
02:04:05,021 --> 02:04:06,606
I'm going on in.

1782
02:04:20,662 --> 02:04:21,746
Kelly?

1783
02:04:29,171 --> 02:04:30,213
Kelly?

1784
02:04:37,053 --> 02:04:39,389
Kelly, you in there?

1785
02:05:03,497 --> 02:05:04,998
Oh, my God.

1786
02:05:08,919 --> 02:05:09,920
Oh, my...

1787
02:05:18,887 --> 02:05:19,888
Oh...

1788
02:05:21,890 --> 02:05:22,891
Oh.

1789
02:05:31,107 --> 02:05:32,234
Oh.

1790
02:05:34,361 --> 02:05:35,445
Oh.

1791
02:05:39,074 --> 02:05:41,117
I'll call the police, Ace.

1792
02:05:59,135 --> 02:06:00,345
Oh, God.

1793
02:07:37,734 --> 02:07:40,570
Go home! Go home!

1794
02:07:41,571 --> 02:07:46,076
Go home! Go home! Go home!

1795
02:07:46,785 --> 02:07:50,413
Ace, there's no police around.
We'd better get out of here.

1796
02:07:52,082 --> 02:07:53,208
Hey, look.

1797
02:08:01,299 --> 02:08:02,759
Doesn't look too good, boy.

1798
02:08:06,096 --> 02:08:09,099
Go home! Go home!

1799
02:08:09,891 --> 02:08:11,309
Come on, take it easy.

1800
02:08:44,384 --> 02:08:46,094
We're getting help, Ace.

1801
02:08:59,858 --> 02:09:01,901
- You okay, boy?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

1802
02:09:01,985 --> 02:09:03,236
You all right?

1803
02:09:03,319 --> 02:09:04,404
Yeah.

1804
02:09:05,029 --> 02:09:06,406
Listen, I'm going to...

1805
02:09:07,449 --> 02:09:09,617
I want you to take care of everything.
Will you?

1806
02:09:09,659 --> 02:09:11,327
- Oh, yeah, I'll get it...
- Okay.

1807
02:09:12,370 --> 02:09:13,538
I'll see you later.

1808
02:10:01,544 --> 02:10:02,670
Hey, where's Hana-ogi?

1809
02:10:02,712 --> 02:10:03,963
Hana-ogi's not here.

1810
02:10:04,047 --> 02:10:05,673
Oh, I know she's here.

1811
02:10:05,715 --> 02:10:07,258
She is on her way Tokyo.

1812
02:10:07,342 --> 02:10:09,719
No, she wasn't... She wasn't
supposed to go to Tokyo till next week.

1813
02:10:09,761 --> 02:10:10,970
She went today.

1814
02:10:11,054 --> 02:10:12,514
I don't believe you.

1815
02:10:12,555 --> 02:10:14,724
- Mr. Gruver...
- I don't believe you.

1816
02:10:14,891 --> 02:10:15,892
I don't care...

1817
02:11:02,981 --> 02:11:04,315
Hana-ogi?

1818
02:11:14,951 --> 02:11:17,996
Hana-ogi. Hana-ogi.

1819
02:11:18,663 --> 02:11:19,956
Hana-ogi.

1820
02:11:30,383 --> 02:11:31,467
Hana-ogi?

1821
02:11:38,850 --> 02:11:40,184
Gruver-san!

1822
02:11:40,268 --> 02:11:42,478
-Hey, where's Hana-ogi?
- She's gone.

1823
02:11:42,520 --> 02:11:44,022
- Where's her room?
-She's gone.

1824
02:11:44,105 --> 02:11:45,940
Listen, where's her room?

1825
02:11:46,858 --> 02:11:48,192
Come here.

1826
02:11:51,905 --> 02:11:54,032
Hana-ogi really gone, Major.

1827
02:11:54,490 --> 02:11:56,284
I don't believe you.

1828
02:11:57,035 --> 02:11:58,453
Hana-ogi.

1829
02:12:04,584 --> 02:12:06,336
I give you my word.

1830
02:12:07,003 --> 02:12:08,922
You go now, too, Major.

1831
02:12:09,756 --> 02:12:11,090
It's over.

1832
02:12:12,258 --> 02:12:14,510
Listen, leave me
alone a minute, will you?

1833
02:12:31,027 --> 02:12:34,364
The hoodlums who attacked
you weren't all your Japanese neighbors.

1834
02:12:34,614 --> 02:12:36,699
For the most part, they were
professional troublemakers

1835
02:12:36,741 --> 02:12:40,203
sent to your street
to create an incident specifically with you.

1836
02:12:40,995 --> 02:12:42,914
Now, if you're important
to those who hate us,

1837
02:12:43,873 --> 02:12:46,417
don't you see how
important you are to us?

1838
02:12:49,379 --> 02:12:51,381
Do you understand
any of this, Lloyd?

1839
02:12:54,550 --> 02:12:56,302
I know how you feel.

1840
02:12:56,636 --> 02:12:57,887
It was...

1841
02:12:58,680 --> 02:13:01,474
It was dreadful about
your friend Kelly and...

1842
02:13:02,642 --> 02:13:03,935
And his wife.

1843
02:13:06,437 --> 02:13:08,231
Must be hard to take.

1844
02:13:10,858 --> 02:13:11,943
And I...

1845
02:13:12,026 --> 02:13:16,322
I hate to tell you
something else, because it's

1846
02:13:17,240 --> 02:13:19,242
almost too grotesque.

1847
02:13:22,578 --> 02:13:24,831
Almost unforgivable in
your eyes, I imagine.

1848
02:13:25,748 --> 02:13:27,500
I got word today that...

1849
02:13:29,168 --> 02:13:31,754
There's a law being passed
in a month or two

1850
02:13:32,714 --> 02:13:35,216
that will make it possible
for men like Kelly

1851
02:13:36,300 --> 02:13:40,138
to take their
Japanese brides back to the States.

1852
02:13:44,726 --> 02:13:46,269
That can't be true, General.

1853
02:13:46,811 --> 02:13:49,397
Well, it happens
to be true, Lloyd.

1854
02:13:54,944 --> 02:13:56,195
Listen.

1855
02:13:57,071 --> 02:13:59,615
How do you get
the guts to come here and tell me that?

1856
02:14:00,575 --> 02:14:03,244
It takes time to get
laws passed, Lloyd.

1857
02:14:03,286 --> 02:14:07,457
And a lot of people have died
in this world needlessly, waiting for them.

1858
02:14:08,666 --> 02:14:09,709
Well, it's...

1859
02:14:09,792 --> 02:14:12,462
It's harder to take
when it hits you personally.

1860
02:14:15,506 --> 02:14:16,632
Lloyd...

1861
02:14:17,800 --> 02:14:19,969
You're lost. You're confused.

1862
02:14:21,971 --> 02:14:25,391
Don't you think it's time you got back
to the main stream of your life?

1863
02:14:26,017 --> 02:14:27,143
Back to your roots?

1864
02:14:27,185 --> 02:14:29,145
What you were born for,
and raised for?

1865
02:14:30,646 --> 02:14:32,607
You'll feel better
about everything when you get back home,

1866
02:14:32,648 --> 02:14:34,609
back to your work.

1867
02:14:37,904 --> 02:14:39,739
Appreciate you
coming over, General.

1868
02:15:22,115 --> 02:15:24,325
Take me to the airport, Mike.

1869
02:15:30,206 --> 02:15:31,999
That must be him.

1870
02:15:32,500 --> 02:15:34,043
Would you hold it,
so we can get a picture, General?

1871
02:15:34,127 --> 02:15:36,671
- Where would you like me? Right here?
-What about there? Yeah.

1872
02:15:38,756 --> 02:15:39,882
Smile, please.

1873
02:15:46,472 --> 02:15:48,349
Hey, Bill, isn't
that Ace Gruver?

1874
02:15:49,308 --> 02:15:50,393
Looks like him.

1875
02:15:53,229 --> 02:15:54,313
Sir?

1876
02:15:55,565 --> 02:15:58,151
Excuse me, aren't
you Major Gruver? Ace Gruver?

1877
02:15:58,234 --> 02:15:59,360
Yes, that's right.

1878
02:15:59,402 --> 02:16:00,736
Well, we're
from Stars and Stripes.

1879
02:16:00,820 --> 02:16:02,238
What are you doing
in Tokyo?

1880
02:16:02,864 --> 02:16:05,449
Well, I'm just passing
through, boys.

1881
02:16:05,533 --> 02:16:07,034
Just seeing the sights, huh?

1882
02:16:07,076 --> 02:16:10,580
That's right. Listen, I'm in a hurry.
Do you mind if I excuse myself?

1883
02:16:10,621 --> 02:16:12,415
- You're excused.
-Sorry.

1884
02:18:30,886 --> 02:18:31,929
Lloyd-san.

1885
02:18:54,285 --> 02:18:55,911
Hello, Hana-ogi.

1886
02:18:59,165 --> 02:19:01,751
I'm going back to
America on Friday.

1887
02:19:03,169 --> 02:19:05,087
And I probably won't

1888
02:19:06,297 --> 02:19:08,257
get back in Japan again.

1889
02:19:11,427 --> 02:19:13,804
And before I go,
there was just...

1890
02:19:15,681 --> 02:19:17,767
Just one thing
I wanted to know.

1891
02:19:20,770 --> 02:19:23,439
You remember one
time you said to me...

1892
02:19:25,983 --> 02:19:27,985
That you could love me

1893
02:19:29,945 --> 02:19:32,114
and be a wife and a mother?

1894
02:19:33,783 --> 02:19:35,117
I remember.

1895
02:19:38,079 --> 02:19:41,290
You said that since
you'd known me, you'd been afraid

1896
02:19:42,625 --> 02:19:44,960
of being
a lonely old woman, teaching dancing.

1897
02:19:45,795 --> 02:19:47,296
Remember that?

1898
02:19:48,798 --> 02:19:50,174
I remember.

1899
02:19:51,967 --> 02:19:55,054
Did you mean that
when you said it, Hana-ogi?

1900
02:19:56,597 --> 02:19:57,973
I meant it.

1901
02:19:58,891 --> 02:20:00,768
It is already happening.

1902
02:20:00,810 --> 02:20:03,979
Love has gone out
of my work, out of me.

1903
02:20:05,689 --> 02:20:08,150
Oh, Lloyd, please go now.

1904
02:20:09,068 --> 02:20:11,654
This will only
bring pain and trouble.

1905
02:20:14,156 --> 02:20:15,408
Hana-ogi,

1906
02:20:16,617 --> 02:20:18,786
you and I are going
to have more trouble

1907
02:20:18,828 --> 02:20:20,830
than we ever
thought of having in our whole lives

1908
02:20:20,871 --> 02:20:23,833
unless you're
absolutely honest with yourself.

1909
02:20:26,669 --> 02:20:30,172
Please, Lloyd, can't we
talk about this later?

1910
02:20:32,842 --> 02:20:34,844
There isn't
going to be any later.

1911
02:20:34,927 --> 02:20:36,887
There's only going
to be right now.

1912
02:20:37,930 --> 02:20:38,931
Oh, uh,

1913
02:20:39,181 --> 02:20:40,182
excuse me, Mother.

1914
02:20:41,308 --> 02:20:42,309
Excuse me.

1915
02:20:45,938 --> 02:20:47,606
I must return this robe.

1916
02:20:47,690 --> 02:20:49,066
Listen to me.

1917
02:20:49,150 --> 02:20:53,028
I want to know.
Do you love me, or don't you?

1918
02:20:55,114 --> 02:20:57,032
Because if you don't,

1919
02:20:57,116 --> 02:20:59,743
then I'm going to
have to find a way to live with it.

1920
02:21:00,828 --> 02:21:02,872
- And if you do, then...
- Please, Lloyd.

1921
02:21:05,207 --> 02:21:07,501
Wait a minute.
Wait a minute.

1922
02:21:11,005 --> 02:21:14,383
Now, I don't want you
to tell me anything more,

1923
02:21:14,425 --> 02:21:18,095
or anything less than
you feel in the very deepest part of you.

1924
02:21:19,263 --> 02:21:20,890
Because what you
answer to me now

1925
02:21:20,931 --> 02:21:23,642
is going to affect us
for the rest of our lives.

1926
02:21:26,604 --> 02:21:29,273
Do you love me, Hana-ogi,
or don't you love me?

1927
02:21:33,444 --> 02:21:35,738
I'm so frightened
and confused.

1928
02:21:36,405 --> 02:21:37,948
I cannot think.

1929
02:21:38,240 --> 02:21:40,242
I cannot even
understand your thinking.

1930
02:21:40,326 --> 02:21:42,036
I'm not thinking!
I'm not thinking...

1931
02:21:42,077 --> 02:21:45,372
For the first time in my life,
I'm not thinking, and I don't care.

1932
02:21:46,916 --> 02:21:49,001
But, Lloyd, we must
do the right thing.

1933
02:21:49,084 --> 02:21:51,754
Oh, what are you talking
about, the right thing?

1934
02:21:51,837 --> 02:21:53,589
We've been wasting
two good lives

1935
02:21:53,672 --> 02:21:54,798
trying to do
the right thing.

1936
02:21:54,882 --> 02:21:56,258
The right thing
for Matsubayashi,

1937
02:21:56,342 --> 02:21:58,928
the right thing
for my father,

1938
02:21:58,969 --> 02:22:00,179
the right thing
for the military,

1939
02:22:00,262 --> 02:22:03,098
the right thing for
Japanese tradition.

1940
02:22:03,182 --> 02:22:05,601
The right thing for
the great white race.

1941
02:22:06,435 --> 02:22:08,354
But we have duties
and obligations.

1942
02:22:08,437 --> 02:22:10,189
That's right, we do.

1943
02:22:10,689 --> 02:22:12,066
We have duties
and obligations.

1944
02:22:12,107 --> 02:22:15,277
And the first obligation we have
is to love each other.

1945
02:22:15,361 --> 02:22:19,198
To become man and wife,
and raise some clean, sweet children.

1946
02:22:19,281 --> 02:22:21,492
And give them
the very best that we know how.

1947
02:22:22,409 --> 02:22:24,620
And if we don't
meet that obligation,

1948
02:22:24,662 --> 02:22:26,789
we ain't going to be
any good to anybody.

1949
02:22:27,790 --> 02:22:31,460
We live in different worlds,
come from different races.

1950
02:22:31,919 --> 02:22:33,087
Oh.

1951
02:22:35,130 --> 02:22:37,841
Honey, I want you
to be my wife.

1952
02:22:40,010 --> 02:22:43,472
But what would happen to our children?
What would they be?

1953
02:22:44,056 --> 02:22:45,266
What would they be?

1954
02:22:45,808 --> 02:22:48,060
They'd be half Japanese,
half American.

1955
02:22:48,143 --> 02:22:50,646
They'd be half
yellow and half white.

1956
02:22:51,188 --> 02:22:53,816
They'd be half you,
they'd be half me.

1957
02:22:54,149 --> 02:22:56,443
That's all they're going to be.

1958
02:23:09,623 --> 02:23:12,334
Hana-ogi, I want you
to come with me now.

1959
02:23:14,253 --> 02:23:17,506
I want you to come with me now,
down to the American Consulate,

1960
02:23:19,008 --> 02:23:20,509
here in Tokyo.

1961
02:23:20,926 --> 02:23:24,430
We're gonna filling out those papers,
'cause we've only got a few days

1962
02:23:24,513 --> 02:23:27,182
to get this whole thing done,
and get it out of the way.

1963
02:23:36,483 --> 02:23:37,610
Will you come?

1964
02:23:48,829 --> 02:23:50,873
I'm going to wait
for you outside.

1965
02:24:21,320 --> 02:24:23,614
Didn't I tell you
he'd be here?

1966
02:24:23,697 --> 02:24:25,240
- Look at this crowd!
- Wow!

1967
02:24:25,324 --> 02:24:27,284
And look who's here,
our rivals.

1968
02:24:27,368 --> 02:24:28,410
What do you know?

1969
02:24:28,494 --> 02:24:30,704
Oh, you guys heard
about it, too, huh?

1970
02:24:30,746 --> 02:24:31,789
No secrets.

1971
02:24:31,872 --> 02:24:34,083
-No secrets in this country!
-well, what are you gonna do?

1972
02:24:39,296 --> 02:24:42,341
Hello, Major.
Well, what a coincidence!

1973
02:24:42,424 --> 02:24:44,051
You got a story
for us, sir?

1974
02:24:45,594 --> 02:24:47,763
No. As a matter
of fact, I don't.

1975
02:24:47,805 --> 02:24:50,683
Oh, now, Major, you're
not going to try to deny it, are you?

1976
02:24:50,766 --> 02:24:52,768
- Deny what?
- Well, the story.

1977
02:24:52,810 --> 02:24:55,604
Why won't you give us a story?
You're big news now, sir.

1978
02:24:55,688 --> 02:24:57,940
I'm afraid I don't know
what you're talking about.

1979
02:25:00,693 --> 02:25:02,361
Here's Hana-ogi.
Maybe she'll talk.

1980
02:25:20,087 --> 02:25:23,465
Come on, Hana-ogi, that's not fair.
What did you say?

1981
02:25:24,717 --> 02:25:28,554
It is very difficult
for a Japanese woman to speak in public.

1982
02:25:29,930 --> 02:25:31,724
I have never done so.

1983
02:25:32,808 --> 02:25:35,018
But perhaps now
it is the time.

1984
02:25:36,770 --> 02:25:39,314
Major Gruver has
asked me to be his...

1985
02:25:39,815 --> 02:25:40,983
His wife.

1986
02:25:45,154 --> 02:25:47,531
He knows there
are many people in his country

1987
02:25:47,614 --> 02:25:50,117
who will be
disturbed by this.

1988
02:25:50,159 --> 02:25:52,786
I know my people
will be shocked, too.

1989
02:25:53,162 --> 02:25:55,998
But I hope they will
learn to understand

1990
02:25:56,707 --> 02:25:58,500
and someday approve.

1991
02:25:59,626 --> 02:26:03,380
We are not afraid
because we know this is right.

1992
02:26:04,715 --> 02:26:07,134
I hope I can
continue as a dancer.

1993
02:26:08,051 --> 02:26:10,179
And I hope, when I am old,

1994
02:26:10,429 --> 02:26:13,223
I will be able to
teach children to dance.

1995
02:26:14,183 --> 02:26:15,517
My own children.

1996
02:26:17,019 --> 02:26:18,145
Major?

1997
02:26:18,187 --> 02:26:20,230
The big brass are
gonna yell their heads off about this.

1998
02:26:20,314 --> 02:26:22,524
And the Japanese
aren't going to like it much, either.

1999
02:26:22,608 --> 02:26:24,902
Have you got anything
to say to them, sir?

2000
02:26:27,362 --> 02:26:28,405
